 475:../../../libs/smtc-hal-mcu-stm32l4/third_party/STM32CubeL4/Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_system.h ****   * @brief  Enable I/O analog switch voltage booster.
 476:../../../libs/smtc-hal-mcu-stm32l4/third_party/STM32CubeL4/Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_system.h ****   * @note   When voltage booster is enabled, I/O analog switches are supplied
 477:../../../libs/smtc-hal-mcu-stm32l4/third_party/STM32CubeL4/Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_system.h ****   *         by a dedicated voltage booster, from VDD power domain. This is
 478:../../../libs/smtc-hal-mcu-stm32l4/third_party/STM32CubeL4/Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_system.h ****   *         the recommended configuration with low VDDA voltage operation.
 479:../../../libs/smtc-hal-mcu-stm32l4/third_party/STM32CubeL4/Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_system.h ****   * @note   The I/O analog switch voltage booster is relevant for peripherals
 480:../../../libs/smtc-hal-mcu-stm32l4/third_party/STM32CubeL4/Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_system.h ****   *         using I/O in analog input: ADC, COMP, OPAMP.
 481:../../../libs/smtc-hal-mcu-stm32l4/third_party/STM32CubeL4/Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_system.h ****   *         However, COMP and OPAMP inputs have a high impedance and
 482:../../../libs/smtc-hal-mcu-stm32l4/third_party/STM32CubeL4/Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_system.h ****   *         voltage booster do not impact performance significantly.
 483:../../../libs/smtc-hal-mcu-stm32l4/third_party/STM32CubeL4/Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_system.h ****   *         Therefore, the voltage booster is mainly intended for
 484:../../../libs/smtc-hal-mcu-stm32l4/third_party/STM32CubeL4/Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_system.h ****   *         usage with ADC.
 485:../../../libs/smtc-hal-mcu-stm32l4/third_party/STM32CubeL4/Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_system.h ****   * @rmtoll SYSCFG_CFGR1 BOOSTEN       LL_SYSCFG_EnableAnalogBooster
